32年在她的家乡享年82岁。"},"hr":{"1450–1532":"1450.–1532.","1454–Male":"1454–preminuo","1502–1579":"1502.–1579","1420–Male":"1420–preminuo","1438–Female":"1438–preminula","1502":"1502.","1579":"1579","1532":"1532.","1455":"1455","1454":"1454","1420":"1420","1450":"1450.","1438":"1438","Westmoreland, England":"Westmorland, England","Hitcham, South Bucks district, Buckinghamshire, England, United Kingdom":"Hitcham, Buckinghamshire, Engleska, United Kingdom"},"cs":{"1450–1532":"1450–1532","1454–Male":"1454–Zesnulý","1502–1579":"1502–1579","1420–Male":"1420–Zesnulý","1438–Female":"1438–Zesnulá","1502":"1502","1579":"1579","1532":"1532","1455":"1455","1454":"1454","1420":"1420","1450":"1450","1438":"1438","Westmoreland, England":"Westmorland, Anglie","Hitcham, South Bucks district, Buckinghamshire, England, United Kingdom":"Hitcham, Buckinghamshire, Anglie, United Kingdom"},"da":{"1450–1532":"1450–1532","1454–Male":"1454–Afdød","1502–1579":"1502–1579","1420–Male":"1420–Afdød","1438–Female":"1438–Afdød","1502":"1502","1579":"1579","1532":"1532","1455":"1455","1454":"1454","1420":"1420","1450":"1450","1438":"1438","Westmoreland, England":"Westmorland, England","Hitcham, South Bucks district, Buckinghamshire, England, United Kingdom":"Hitcham, Buckinghamshire, England, United Kingdom"},"nl":{"1450–1532":"1450–1532","1454–Male":"1454–Overleden","1502–1579":"1502–1579","1420–Male":"1420–Overleden","1438–Female":"1438–Overleden","1502":"1502","1579":"1579","1532":"1532","1455":"1455","1454":"1454","1420":"1420","1450":"1450","1438":"1438","Westmoreland, England":"Westmorland, England","Hitcham, South Bucks district, Buckinghamshire, England, United Kingdom":"Hitcham, Buckinghamshire, Engeland, Verenigd Koninkrijk"},"en":{"1450–1532":"1450–1532","1454–Male":"1454–Deceased","1502–1579":"1502–1579","1420–Male":"1420–Deceased","1438–Female":"1438–Deceased","1502":"1502","1579":"1579","1532":"1532","1455":"1455","1454":"1454","1420":"1420","1450":"1450","1438":"1438","Westmoreland, England":"Westmorland, England","Hitcham, South Bucks district, Buckinghamshire, England, United Kingdom":"Hitcham, Buckinghamshire, England, United Kingdom","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Smyth","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Irish Brendan, Ronan, Aidan, Brigid, Conor, Eoin, Malachy, Paddy.","English: variant of   Smith  . This form of the surname is particularly common Ireland."],"variants":[{"name":"Smith","meanings":["English and Scottish: occupational name denoting a worker in metal, especially iron, such as a blacksmith or farrier, from Middle English <i>smith</i> ‘smith’ (Old English <i>smith</i>, probably a derivative of <i>smītan</i> ‘to strike, hammer’). Early examples are also found in the Latin form   Faber  . Metal-working was one of the earliest occupations for which specialist skills were required, and its importance ensured that this term and its equivalents in other languages were the most widespread of all occupational surnames in Europe. Medieval smiths were important not only in making horseshoes, plowshares, and other domestic articles, but above all for their skill in forging swords, other weapons, and armor. This is also the most frequent of all surnames in the US. It is very common among African Americans and Native Americans (see also 5 below). This surname (in any of the two possible English senses; see also below) is also found in Haiti. See also   Smither  .","English: from Middle English <i>smithe</i> ‘smithy, forge’ (Old English <i>smiththe</i>). The surname may be topographic, for someone who lived in or by a blacksmith's shop, occupational, for someone who worked in one, or habitational, from a place so named, such as Smitha in King's Nympton (Devon). Compare   Smithey  .","Irish and Scottish: sometimes adopted for Gaelic <b>Mac Gobhann</b>, Irish <b>Mac Gabhann</b> ‘son of the smith’. See   McGowan  ."]}]},{"name":"Joan","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Contracted form of Old French <i>Jo(h)anne</i>, from Latin <i>Io(h)anna</i> (  see  Joanna  ). In England this was the usual feminine form of   John   from the Middle English period onwards and was extremely popular, but in the 16th and 17th centuries it steadily lost ground to   Jane .  It was strongly revived in the first part of the 20th century, partly under the influence of  George Bernard Shaw's  play St Joan (  1923 ), based on the life of  Joan of Arc  (  1412–31 ). Claiming to be guided by the voices of the saints, she persuaded the French dauphin to defy the occupying English forces and have himself crowned, and she led the French army that raised the siege of Orleans in  1429 . The following year she was captured by the Burgundians and sold to the English, and a year later she was burned at the stake for witchcraft at the age of 18 or 19. Her story has captured the imagination of many writers, and she is variously portrayed as a national and political hero, a model of apolitical straightforwardness and honesty, and a religious heroine. She was canonized in  1920 . More recent influences have included the American film actress  Joan Crawford  (  1908–77 , born  Lucille le Sueur ), the British actress  Joan Collins  (  b. 1933 ), the American comedienne  Joan Rivers  (  b. 1933 ), and the West Indian pop singer  Joan Armatrading  (  b. 1950 )."],"variants":[{"name":"John","meanings":["Greek: the Lord gave graciously; whom Jehovah gave; whom Jehovah bestowed."]}]},{"name":"Ann","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Variant spelling of   Anne .  In the U.S. <i>Ann</i> is the more frequent spelling."],"variants":[]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705197,"age":5,"year":"1455","julianDay":2252488,"title":"Wars of the Roses","description":"Wars of the Roses was a series of English civil wars for control of the throne of England between the royal families House of Lancaster and the House of York. The name of the war was derived as the red rose was the symbol of the Lancastrians and the white rose was the symbol of the Yorks.","url":"https://www.history.com/topics/british-history/wars-of-the-roses","urlTitle":"History - Wars of the Roses","jurisdictionLevel":1}],"lifeSummary":"When Joan Ann Smyth was born in 1450, in Westmorland, England, her father, William Smyth, was 31 and her mother, Ann, was 12. She had at least 1 son with Ralph Ramsey. She died in 1532, in her hometown, at the age of 82."},"et":{"1450–1532":"1450–1532","1454–Male":"1454–Surnud","1502–1579":"1502–1579","1420–Male":"1420–Surnud","1438–Female":"1438–Surnud","1502":"1502","1579":"1579","1532":"1532","1455":"1455","1454":"1454","1420":"1420","1450":"1450","1438":"1438","Westmoreland, England":"Westmorland, England","Hitcham, South Bucks district, Buckinghamshire, England, United Kingdom":"Hitcham, Buckinghamshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1450–1532":"1450–1532","1454–Male":"1454–Kuollut","1502–1579":"1502–1579","1420–Male":"1420–Kuollut","1438–Female":"1438–Kuollut","1502":"1502","1579":"1579","1532":"1532","1455":"1455","1454":"1454","1420":"1420","1450":"1450","1438":"1438","Westmoreland, England":"Westmorland, England","Hitcham, South Bucks district, Buckinghamshire, England, United Kingdom":"Hitcham, Buckinghamshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"1450–1532":"1450–1532","1454–Male":"1454–Décédé","1502–1579":"1502–1579","1420–Male":"1420–Décédé","1438–Female":"1438–Décédée","1502":"1502","1579":"1579","1532":"1532","1455":"1455","1454":"1454","1420":"1420","1450":"1450","1438":"1438","Westmoreland, England":"Westmorland, Angleterre","Hitcham, South Bucks district, Buckinghamshire, England, United Kingdom":"Hitcham, Buckinghamshire, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","lifeSummary":"Lorsque Joan Ann Smyth est née en 1450, à Westmorland, Angleterre, son père, William Smyth, avait 31 ans et sa mère, Ann, avait 12 ans. Elle a eu au moins 1 fils avec Ralph Ramsey. Elle est décédée en 1532, dans sa ville natale, à l’âge de 82 ans."},"de":{"1450–1532":"1450–1532","1454–Male":"1454–Verstorben","1502–1579":"1502–1579","1420–Male":"1420–Verstorben","1438–Female":"1438–Verstorben","1502":"1502","1579":"1579","1532":"1532","1455":"1455","1454":"1454","1420":"1420","1450":"1450","1438":"1438","Westmoreland, England":"Westmorland, England","Hitcham, South Bucks district, Buckinghamshire, England, United Kingdom":"Hitcham, Buckinghamshire, England, United Kingdom","lifeSummary":"Als Joan Ann Smyth 1450 in Westmorland, England geboren wurde, war ihr Vater William Smyth 31 und ihre Mutter Ann 12. Sie hatte mit Ralph Ramsey mindestens 1 Sohn. Sie starb 1532 im Alter von 82 Jahren in ihrem Geburtsort."},"ht":{"1450–1532":"1450–1532","1454–Male":"1454–Desede","1502–1579":"1502–1579","1420–Male":"1420–Desede","1438–Female":"1438–Desede","1502":"1502","1579":"1579","1532":"1532","1455":"1455","1454":"1454","1420":"1420","1450":"1450","1438":"1438","Westmoreland, England":"Westmorland, England","Hitcham, South Bucks district, Buckinghamshire, England, United Kingdom":"Hitcham, Buckinghamshire, Angletè, United Kingdom"},"hu":{"1450–1532":"1450–1532","1454–Male":"1454–elhunyt","1502–1579":"1502–1579","1420–Male":"1420–elhunyt","1438–Female":"1438–elhunyt","1502":"1502","1579":"1579","1532":"1532","1455":"1455","1454":"1454","1420":"1420","1450":"1450","1438":"1438","Westmoreland, England":"Westmorland, England","Hitcham, South Bucks district, Buckinghamshire, England, United Kingdom":"Hitcham, Buckinghamshire, Anglia, United Kingdom"},"id":{"1450–1532":"1450–1532","1454–Male":"1454–Telah Meninggal","1502–1579":"1502–1579","1420–Male":"1420–Telah Meninggal","1438–Female":"1438–Telah Meninggal","1502":"1502","1579":"1579","1532":"1532","1455":"1455","1454":"1454","1420":"1420","1450":"1450","1438":"1438","Westmoreland, England":"Westmorland, England","Hi